    @* ── What Is FreeServicesHub? ─────────────────────────────────── *@
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-primary bg-opacity-10">
            <h4 class="mb-0"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info me-2 text-primary"></i>What Is FreeServicesHub?</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>
                <strong>FreeServicesHub</strong> is a free, open-source service-agent management platform built on
                .NET 10. It monitors remote Windows services by collecting real-time CPU, memory, and disk metrics,
                then displays them on a live Blazor dashboard powered by SignalR.
            </p>
            <p>
                The system is built on the <strong>FreeCRM framework</strong> — inheriting its authentication,
                multi-tenancy, plugin system, EF Core data layer, and SignalR infrastructure.
                Everything new follows the <code>.App.</code> extension-file pattern so the base framework
                can be updated independently.
            </p>
            <div class="row mt-3">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-server me-1 text-success"></i> Hub</h6>
                    <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                        Blazor Server + WebAssembly app. Receives agent heartbeats via SignalR,
                        stores metrics in a multi-provider database (SQL Server, MySQL, PostgreSQL,
                        SQLite, or InMemory), and pushes live updates to connected dashboards.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-microchip me-1 text-warning"></i> Agent</h6>
                    <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                        .NET Worker Service that runs as a Windows Service. Collects system snapshots
                        every 30 seconds, sends heartbeats to the hub over SignalR, and falls back to
                        HTTP POST + local logging when disconnected.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-wrench me-1 text-info"></i> Installer</h6>
                    <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                        Dual-mode CLI tool. Interactive menu for developers; headless mode for CI/CD
                        pipelines. Builds, deploys, configures, and manages the agent as a Windows Service
                        using <code>sc.exe</code>.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    @* ── Two-Key Trust Chain ──────────────────────────────────────── *@
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-warning bg-opacity-10">
            <h4 class="mb-0"><i class="fa-solid fa-key me-2 text-warning"></i>Two-Key Trust Chain</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>Security between the hub and agents uses two cryptographic keys with distinct lifecycles:</p>
            <div class="table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm table-bordered">
                    <thead class="table-light">
                        <tr>
                            <th>Key Type</th>
                            <th>Created By</th>
                            <th>Given To</th>
                            <th>Stored As</th>
                            <th>Lifetime</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Registration Key</strong></td>
                            <td>Hub (via CI/CD or UI)</td>
                            <td>Pipeline → Agent</td>
                            <td>SHA-256 hash in DB</td>
                            <td>24 hours, one-time-use, burns on use</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>API Client Token</strong></td>
                            <td>Hub (during registration)</td>
                            <td>Agent</td>
                            <td>SHA-256 hash in DB</td>
                            <td>Until revoked from Hub UI</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
<pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 rounded" style="font-size: 0.75rem; overflow-x: auto;">
Pipeline                        Hub                         Agent
   │                             │                            │
   │── GenerateRegistrationKeys ─▶│                            │
   │◀─ [Key A, Key B] ──────────│                            │
   │                             │  (stores hashes, 24hr exp) │
   │── deploys Key A to ────────▶│                            │
   │                             │                   Agent starts
   │                             │◀── RegisterAgent (Key A) ──│
   │                             │    validate, burn key       │
   │                             │    generate API token       │
   │                             │── Token X (plaintext) ────▶│
   │                             │    (stores hash in DB)      │ (stores in config)
   │                             │                            │
   │                             │◀── heartbeat (Token X) ────│
   │                             │◀── heartbeat (Token X) ────│
</pre>
            <p class="small text-muted mt-2 mb-0">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved me-1"></i>
                The raw API token is <strong>never</strong> stored server-side. Only the SHA-256 hash is persisted.
                The token is returned exactly <strong>once</strong> at registration time.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    @* ── Agent Communication Flow ─────────────────────────────────── *@
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-success bg-opacity-10">
            <h4 class="mb-0"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrows-left-right me-2 text-success"></i>Agent ↔ Hub Communication</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
<pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 rounded" style="font-size: 0.72rem; overflow-x: auto; line-height: 1.4;">
              AGENT                                       HUB
         (Windows Service)                        (Blazor + SignalR)

┌────────────────────┐
│  Agent starts up   │
│  No ApiClientToken │
└────────┬───────────┘
         │
STEP 1:  │  POST /api/Data/RegisterAgent
REGISTER │  { RegistrationKey, Hostname, OS, Arch, Version }
         │ ────────────────────────────────────────────────▶ Validate → Create → Token
         │ ◀──────────────────────────────────────────────── { ApiClientToken: "raw-..." }
         │
STEP 2:  │  WebSocket: /freeserviceshubHub?access_token=raw-...
SIGNALR  │ ────────────────────────────────────────────────▶ ApiKeyMiddleware → SHA256 → DB
         │  JoinGroup("Agents")
         │
STEP 3:  │  ┌──── every 30 seconds ────────┐
HEARTBEAT│  │  CollectSnapshot()            │
  LOOP   │  │  CPU, RAM, Drives, Uptime    │
         │  │  SendHeartbeat(hub) ──────────────────────────▶ SaveHeartbeat → DB
         │  │                               │                 Broadcast → "AgentMonitor"
         │  └───────────────────────────────┘                       │
         │                                                          ▼
         │                                               ┌────────────────────┐
         │                                               │  Blazor Dashboard  │
SHUTDOWN │ ◀──── hub sends "Shutdown" ───────────────────│  ● DEV-01  Online  │
         │  → Program.Lifetime.StopApplication()         │  ● PROD-01 Online  │
         │                                               └────────────────────┘
</pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    @* ── Background Services ──────────────────────────────────────── *@
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-info bg-opacity-10">
            <h4 class="mb-0"><i class="fa-solid fa-gears me-2 text-info"></i>Background Services</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>Three hub-side background services run continuously. Their logs are viewable on the
               <a href="@Helpers.BuildUrl("BackgroundServices")">Background Services</a> page in real time.</p>
            <div class="row g-3">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="card border-success h-100">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-binoculars me-1 text-success"></i> AgentMonitorService</h6>
                            <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                                Polls every 5 seconds. Loads all agents, compares each agent's
                                <code>LastHeartbeat</code> against the stale threshold.
                                Detects status transitions (Online → Stale → Offline) and broadcasts
                                changes to the <code>AgentMonitor</code> SignalR group. Uses exponential
                                backoff on errors (5s × multiplier, max 60s).
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="card border-warning h-100">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-seedling me-1 text-warning"></i> DevRegistrationKeySeeder</h6>
                            <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                                Runs once on startup in Development mode only.
                                Seeds a known registration key (<code>dev-test-key-seed</code>) into the
                                InMemory database so the Aspire-orchestrated agent can auto-register
                                without manual key generation.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="card border-info h-100">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h6><i class="fa-solid fa-clock me-1 text-info"></i> BackgroundProcessor</h6>
                            <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                                Configurable scheduled processor. Enabled via
                                <code>BackgroundService:Enabled</code> in appsettings.
                                Supports load balancing by hostname filter.
                                Processes queued work items at a configurable interval.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    @* ── Data Layer ───────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-secondary bg-opacity-10">
            <h4 class="mb-0"><i class="fa-solid fa-database me-2 text-secondary"></i>Data Layer</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
<pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 rounded" style="font-size: 0.72rem; overflow-x: auto; line-height: 1.4;">
┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  EFDataModel : DbContext  (partial class pattern)                        │
│                                                                           │
│  App Tables:                           Base Tables:                       │
│    Agents              (registered)      Departments     Users            │
│    AgentHeartbeats     (time-series)     Settings        Tenants          │
│    RegistrationKeys    (SHA-256 hash)    FileStorages    UserGroups       │
│    ApiClientTokens     (SHA-256 hash)    Tags / TagItems                 │
│                                                                           │
│  Providers:                                                               │
│    ├── InMemory    (dev / Aspire)                                         │
│    ├── SQL Server  (production)                                           │
│    ├── MySQL                                                              │
│    ├── PostgreSQL                                                         │
│    └── SQLite                                                             │
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

IDataAccess (interface)
  RegisterAgent(request, tenantId) → AgentRegistrationResponse
  SaveHeartbeat(heartbeat)         → BooleanResponse
  GetAgents(ids, tenantId, user)   → List&lt;Agent&gt;
  GenerateRegistrationKeys(...)    → List&lt;RegistrationKey&gt;
  GetApiClientTokens(tenantId)     → List&lt;ApiClientToken&gt;
  RevokeApiClientToken(id, user)   → BooleanResponse
</pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    @* ── SignalR Groups ───────────────────────────────────────────── *@
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-danger bg-opacity-10">
            <h4 class="mb-0"><i class="fa-solid fa-tower-broadcast me-2 text-danger"></i>SignalR Real-Time Communication</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm table-bordered">
                    <thead class="table-light">
                        <tr><th>Group</th><th>Members</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><code>Agents</code></td>
                            <td>Connected agent instances</td>
                            <td>Receive shutdown commands, broadcast messages</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><code>AgentMonitor</code></td>
                            <td>Dashboard UI clients</td>
                            <td>Receive live agent status updates, heartbeat data</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><code>BackgroundServiceLogs</code></td>
                            <td>Background Services page viewers</td>
                            <td>Real-time log streaming from hub-side services</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><code>&lt;TenantId&gt;</code></td>
                            <td>Tenant-scoped users</td>
                            <td>Tenant-specific data change notifications</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <h6 class="mt-3">Message Types</h6>
            <div class="table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm table-bordered">
                    <thead class="table-light">
                        <tr><th>Direction</th><th>Type</th><th>Content</th></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td>Agent → Hub</td><td>SendHeartbeat</td><td>CPU, RAM, disk, uptime snapshot</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Hub → Agent</td><td>Shutdown</td><td>Graceful shutdown command</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Hub → Dashboard</td><td>AgentHeartbeat</td><td>All agents with latest status</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Hub → Dashboard</td><td>AgentStatusChanged</td><td>Status transition detected</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Hub → Dashboard</td><td>AgentConnected</td><td>New agent registered and online</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Hub → Dashboard</td><td>AgentDisconnected</td><td>Agent went offline</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>Hub → Dashboard</td><td>BackgroundServiceLog</td><td>Real-time log entry from services</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    @* ── Deployment Pipeline ──────────────────────────────────────── *@
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-primary bg-opacity-10">
            <h4 class="mb-0"><i class="fa-solid fa-rocket me-2 text-primary"></i>Deployment Pipeline (12-Step Lifecycle)</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
<pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 rounded" style="font-size: 0.72rem; overflow-x: auto; line-height: 1.4;">
STEP  ACTION                        ACTOR           DETAIL
────  ────────────────────────────  ──────────────  ─────────────────────────────────────
  1   Generate registration keys    Pipeline → Hub  N keys for N servers, 24hr, one-use
  2   Shutdown agents               Hub → Agents    "Shutdown" via SignalR
  3   Agents confirm shutdown       Each agent      Graceful stop, confirm
  4   Hub reports all offline       Hub             Pipeline waits
  5   Shutdown hub                  Pipeline        Stop hub process
  6   Deploy hub                    Pipeline        Install new build, start hub
  7   Hub comes online              Hub             Reconnect to DB, hashes persist
  8   Deploy agents                 Pipeline        Install on each server, inject key
  9   Agents start                  Each agent      Read registration key from config
 10   Agents register               Agent → Hub     One-time key consumed, token returned
 11   Agents store token            Each agent      Save to config, begin heartbeat
 12   Dashboard shows online        Hub             AgentMonitorService pushes to UI
</pre>
            <p class="small text-muted mt-2 mb-0">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-clock me-1"></i>
                Timing: ~5 minutes total. Azure DevOps YAML pipeline with parallel build stages.
                Web app, agent, and installer build in parallel, then deploy sequentially.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    @* ── Agent Reconnection Strategy ──────────────────────────────── *@
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-warning bg-opacity-10">
            <h4 class="mb-0"><i class="fa-solid fa-rotate me-2 text-warning"></i>Agent Reconnection Strategy</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>The agent uses <code>ExponentialBackoffRetryPolicy : IRetryPolicy</code> that never gives up:</p>
            <div class="table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm table-bordered" style="max-width: 400px;">
                    <thead class="table-light">
                        <tr><th>Attempt</th><th>Delay</th><th>Action</th></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr><td>1</td><td>2s</td><td>Reconnect via SignalR</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>2</td><td>4s</td><td>Reconnect via SignalR</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>3</td><td>8s</td><td>Reconnect via SignalR</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>4</td><td>16s</td><td>Reconnect via SignalR</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>5+</td><td>30s (cap)</td><td>Reconnect via SignalR</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                When disconnected, the agent buffers heartbeats locally and flushes them on reconnect.
                If SignalR is unavailable, it falls back to HTTP POST. If both fail, it logs to
                <code>agent.log</code> (rolling file, 5 MB cap) and retries next cycle.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    @* ── Request Pipeline ─────────────────────────────────────────── *@
    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-secondary bg-opacity-10">
            <h4 class="mb-0"><i class="fa-solid fa-diagram-project me-2 text-secondary"></i>Request Pipeline</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
<pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 rounded" style="font-size: 0.72rem; overflow-x: auto; line-height: 1.4;">
Incoming Request
     │
     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              ApiKeyMiddleware                        │
│                                                     │
│   /api/agent/*        → requires Bearer token       │
│   /freeserviceshubHub → requires Bearer token       │
│   /api/Data/*         → pass through to Blazor auth │
│   /health             → pass through (anonymous)    │
│   everything else     → pass through (Blazor UI)    │
│                                                     │
│   Token: SHA-256(raw) → lookup ApiClientTokens DB   │
│   Match? → ClaimsPrincipal(AgentId, TenantId)       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
     │
     ├──────────────────────┐
     ▼                      ▼
┌──────────────┐    ┌───────────────┐
│  REST API    │    │  SignalR Hub  │
│  Controller  │    │  Endpoint    │
└──────────────┘    └───────────────┘
</pre>
        </div>
    </div>

